&lt;p&gt;You can use the &lt;code&gt;pivot&lt;/code&gt; functionality to arrange the data in a nice table&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-py s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-python&quot;&gt;df.groupby([&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&apos;Fruit&apos;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&apos;Name&apos;&lt;/span&gt;],as_index = &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-literal&quot;&gt;False&lt;/span&gt;).&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-built_in&quot;&gt;sum&lt;/span&gt;().pivot(&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&apos;Fruit&apos;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&apos;Name&apos;&lt;/span&gt;).fillna(&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-number&quot;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;)



